t.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a small UNIX command interpreter (executable: hsh)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
.B echo "command" | hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program implements a minimal subset of
.BR /bin/sh (1)
behavior:
.IP \[bu] 2
Interactive prompt + REPL loop, and non-interactive (stdin-driven) mode.
.IP \[bu]
PATH search for commands that do not contain '/'.
.IP \[bu]
Built-ins:
.BR env ,
.BR "exit [n]" .
.IP \[bu]
Error messages include program name and line number.
.IP \[bu]
Code follows Betty style; no file contains more than 5 functions.

.SH TASKS OVERVIEW
.TP
.B Task 0 — README, man, AUTHORS
Supply
.B README.md ,
this manual page
.BR (man_1_simple_shell) ,
and an
.B AUTHORS
file listing contributors.
.TP
.B Task 1 — Betty would be proud
All files pass Betty checks; each file has \<= 5 functions.
.TP
.B Task 2 — Simple Shell 0.1
Display a prompt, read a single-word command, execute via
.BR fork (2)
/ 
.BR execve (2) .
Loop until EOF or
.BR exit .
.TP
.B Task 3 — Simple Shell 0.2
Search the command in the
.B PATH
environment variable (if it has no '/').
If not found, print an error (see ERRORS).
.TP
.B Task 4 — Simple Shell 0.3
Handle end-of-file (Ctrl+D) cleanly without crashing or infinite loops.
.TP
.B Task 5 — Simple Shell 0.4
Implement
.BR "exit [n]" .
If
.I n
is not a valid number, print an "Illegal number" error and do not exit; return status 2.
.TP
.B Task 6 — Simple Shell 1.0
Implement
.BR env
to print the current environment (reads from
.BR environ ).

.SH BUILT-INS
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables, one per line.
.TP
.B exit [n]
Exit the shell with status
.I n
(modulo 256). If
.I n
is not a valid number, print the error shown in
.BR ERRORS ,
do not exit, and set status to 2.

.SH USAGE
.SS Interactive mode
.PP
.EX
$ ./hsh
$ /bin/ls
file1.c  file2.c  README.md
$ exit
.EE
.SS Non-interactive mode
.PP
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1.c  file2.c  README.md
.EE

.SH ERRORS
When a command is not found:
.PP
.EX
hsh: line_number: command: not found
.EE
When
.BR exit
receives an invalid numeric argument:
.PP
.EX
exit
hsh: line_number: exit: Illegal number: arg
.EE

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell exits with the status of the last executed command.
On invalid numeric argument to
.BR exit ,
the shell does not terminate and sets the status to 2.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B README.md
Project description and task overview.
.TP
.B man_1_simple_shell
This manual page.
.TP
.B AUTHORS
List of contributors in the form "Name <email>".
.TP
.B shell.h
Public header (macros, types, prototypes).
.TP
.B builtins.c
Built-in commands:
.BR env ,
.BR exit ,
and dispatch.
.TP
.B path.c
PATH resolution for commands without '/'.
.TP
.B exec.c
Process creation and execution via
.BR fork (2)
/ 
.BR execve (2) .
.TP
.B parser.c , helpers.c , utils*.c
Tokenization and small utilities.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR getenv (3)

